runs.comm: walks down the pitch to a length ball and squeezes it behind point, decides to come back for the second and makes it in time
beaten, he likes to punch off the back foot, this one leaves him from a length
full and swinging in, flicked away, in the air, past midwicket, who runs after it and pulls it back just inside the rope
quietly works a length ball from off to midwicket
holds its line now as it bounces from a good length outside off, pushed to covers
hit on the thigh pad as he fails to work a back of a length ball to leg, they take the single as the ball rolls to the off side
straightens after being angled across outside off, good length, slapped away from the crease, Warner gets behind it to his right at point
swings in from a fuller length, and carries down leg

that has to be very close, and Nazir has to go back, straightening right on the stumps, Nazir hit on the pad on the forward push, looked out on first look, pitched off, swung in, struck him just below the knee roll in front of middle and leg
pushes with the away swing from him, to covers
goes reaching out for a wide one, and thick-edges it past slip
ducks under a bouncer angled into the left-hander
pitched up, he looks to be in good nick as he eases it calmly to wide mid off
stroked over mid off, straightening around off stump, Hafeez checked his push a bit as he reached out, but timed it quite well in the end, comfortably over mid off
pitched up, he goes reaching outside off for the ball again, and this time his drive finds short extra cover
left alone as it swings in outside off
driven crisply but Warner is too quick at point to cut it off
bowled 'em, ripper, Cummins from wide of the crease, angles it in, swings it in even more, too much for Malik, who goes for the drive, and is bowled through the gate, hit middle and off, top delivery
swings in full again, Kamran goes forward and thumps it hard, but short extra cover saves the boundary with a dive
back of a length, worked to midwicket
stays in the crease and punches a back of a length ball to point
punched wide of extra cover
another one, leading edge, tame ans loopy and straight to mid off, was looking to work a length ball square off the pads, closed the face early, and that was it
beaten, back of a length ball moving away outside off, reaches weakly at it
and again, this time he tries to push away from the body, the ball leaves him
pushes at a length ball angled in, gets it away to third man
right on off, angled across, he pushes softly in front of mid off
holding its line after being angled in outside off, he pushes at it, in the air for a while, to point
from wide of the crease, holds its line again outside off, this is such a difficult angle to play, pushed to cover
pitched up closer to off now, a crisp drive straight to mid off
angled into the pads this time, worked to deep midwicket

excellent judge of a catch Michael Hussey is, and he shows it again, that was a pretty decent stroke, Umar Akmal walked out and created momentum for the flick over midwicket, Hussey was far away from the ball as he sprinted across from deep midwicket to his left, took it some feet from the rope, overbalanced and got still closer to the boundary, and steadied himself calmly
whipped off the pads to deep square
punched to extra cover off the back foot
cut to cover, throw misses at the striker's, direct hit would have been close, but the throw was pretty wide
slower one angled across outside off, beats the outside edge

goes for the pull to one down the leg side, misses, the caught behind appeal is turned down, and it is not called a wide either, hmm, have to see replays, Watson unfortunate not to get that one, replays show it came off the glove, there was a deflection too
comes in from outside off, steered to short third, can;t get the single
down the leg side, rolls behind square leg
slides in to the left-hander with the angle, hits thigh pad and rolls away
turns away sharply, slapped to extra cover, direct hit at the non-striker's gets them one off the ricochet
flighted full driven to long off
goes forward to defend a dipping tossed ball to covers
flat and spinning away, cut past point, sweeper gets across
drives a full delivery to extra cover
pushes a length ball down the pitch
drives a full one back to the bowler
floated down the leg side, off the keeper's pads, could have taken a thin edge, not sure
quick offbreak on middle, blocked
thick edge runs to the third man rope, pulled back in time
enough flight for him to size up the slog sweep, go down on a knee and mow it flat over midwicket
low tossed up full toss, nudged to fine leg
beaten, quicker through the air, angled across from back of the hand, and spins away from the right-hander
beaten in the flight, checks his stroke, on the bounce to midwicket
not picking it, rocks back, makes room, the ball spins away again outside off, cannot reach it
worked off the pad and past short fine's dive

hello, that is one of the softest dismissals you'll see, Jamshed pushing tamely off the back foot straight to extra cover, gentle offspinner from round the stumps, on a length, bounces a bit more, he pushes away from the body, and extra cover jogs in to take the gift
flicked through midwicket
down the leg side
down the leg side
runs it to short third man again
full one patted back to the bowler
spins ins sharply from around off, worked to midwicket

the wrong 'un, leading edge falls short of point, tossed up, from back of the had, turns away from the right hander on middle and off, he was looking to work it to leg, they are not picking him at all
spins in now, hits him on the pad, was going down leg
worked square to leg
and again, wants to drive through extra cover, it carries across with the angle, does not turn in, beaten
beaten on the cut this time, Hogg could play for a few more years surely, terrific control
plays from the crease, surprised as the length ball seems to stop a bit, stabbed down towards long on
slow length ball punched to point
has a swing and misses a length ball which goes quite close to off
moves forward but ends up pushing it back to the bowler
got hold of this one alright, mowed over midwicket from well outside off, seemed to bounce just in front of the rope, just
charges out and slaps a length ball in the air to sweeper cover
pitched up, angled in, driven hard past extra cover's dive, sweeper goes screaming across the turf with his slide, and prevents the four
full toss hit straight to extra cover
plays one angled in sharply from deep in the crease, pushes it towards extra cover
pitched up, defended to extra cover again
very full, he drives down to long off
full ball again, he scythes it to wide long off
tries to drag this one from outside off, it is the slower one, and he is beaten
comes out and works a length ball to wide long on
slower one again, full and on the stumps, he adjusts to squeeze it down to long off
another slower one, whipped to long on
makes some room and guides it behind point, but backward point runs across and dives to take pace off it
drives a full toss to sweeper cover, who keeps them to one
Hogg deserved one, he did, the wrong 'un, they haven't picked him at all, opened up for the pull, it spun away from him, he flailed weakly, got a tame top edge, slip got around to it
appeal for leg before, as he rips this one in to the right-hander, headed down leg probably
swept to deep square leg from outside off
what a ripper, that has kicked across the right-hander from a good length, Razzaq manages a weak smile
could not pick him last ball of his spell as well, tried a big heave, ended up swinging way inside the line, as it angled away
forced straight to midwicket
carts it away to deep midwicket
down the track, and crashes it down the ground, Australia are in no mood to give any boundaries, long off dives and saves it
long off in business again as Gul hits down the ground now
comes out, chops it off the stumps behind point, Gul out by a long way as Wade gathers the throw on the half-volley and takes the bails off
works an offspinner to short fine leg
slow, full and wide, carted high over extra cover with feet wide apart
mstimes the heave to midwicket

the slow bouncer earns Cummins another wicket, a similar delivery had been put away over point by the same batsman in the previous game in the Super Over, this time Razzaq slashes it on his toes, and short third man scrambles to his right to take it
pacy length ball played out to point
avoids a bouncer as he crouches under it
full and angled in, pushed to midwicket
worked wristily from outside off to midwicket
swept from outside off again, to short fine
charges out and heaves through square leg
everyone missed, batsman, ball, keeper, Raza pushed well outside the line of the offbreak, which bounced just over the stumps, and Wade could not gather
pushed to the bowler
punched off the back foot to long off
moves across, right behind the line of a length ball and blocks, pretty decent technique
lets a wide and full go outside off
thick edge as he prods at a widish one that moves in, does not carry to White at wide slip
right forward and smothers a pitched up ball to the off side
full, slow and wide, pushed on the bounce to extra cover
again he is behind the line of a length ball angled in, and defends solidly, end of Cummins' excellent spell, he's come back strongly after that Super Over
got him, fullish and crashes into the stumps from round the wicket, Ajmal looking to work it to leg, misses, and the stumps are on the ground
